{"expireTime":9007200848181577000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-e1d574d2af947dab89ba62f4493db2c6-gatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"It’s not uncommon for people to assume advertising and marketing are the same thing. After all, they are both effective avenues to promote a business or service, and sometimes they overlap. However, advertising and marketing have different approaches and end results. If you are a small business or start-up venture, it’s important to know the specifics of each and how to get the most bang for your buck. This way, you’ll have more to work when strategizing, forecasting and building your business. ","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":2},"end":{"line":2,"column":501,"offset":502},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":2},"end":{"line":2,"column":501,"offset":502},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Advertising 101","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":4,"offset":509},"end":{"line":4,"column":19,"offset":524},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":506},"end":{"line":4,"column":19,"offset":524},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you’ve ever watched Mad Men, you’ve likely got an understanding of ‘classic’ advertising – before the Internet, that is. The main objective is to get a broader audience to buy, subscribe to, or use a product or service. Advertising is usually temporary in nature, but with a call to action or promotion in mind. For example, a company will advertise a new shoe line, handy app, organic cereal, or menu. To be successful, companies needs to understand who their audience is and target them strategically. It also requires a budget – advertising is not free. ","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1,"offset":526},"end":{"line":5,"column":561,"offset":1086},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1,"offset":526},"end":{"line":5,"column":561,"offset":1086},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Popular examples include:","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":1090},"end":{"line":7,"column":26,"offset":1115},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":1090},"end":{"line":7,"column":26,"offset":1115},"indent":[]}},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"start":null,"spread":false,"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Print Advertising: Magazines, brochures, flyers, newspapers ","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":3,"offset":1119},"end":{"line":8,"column":63,"offset":1179},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":3,"offset":1119},"end":{"line":8,"column":63,"offset":1179},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":1117},"end":{"line":8,"column":63,"offset":1179},"indent":[]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Outdoor Advertising: Billboards, banners, flags, benches, bus shelters, wraps ","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":3,"offset":1183},"end":{"line":9,"column":81,"offset":1261},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":3,"offset":1183},"end":{"line":9,"column":81,"offset":1261},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":1181},"end":{"line":9,"column":81,"offset":1261},"indent":[]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Broadcast Advertising: Television, streaming services and radio ","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":3,"offset":1265},"end":{"line":10,"column":67,"offset":1329},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":3,"offset":1265},"end":{"line":10,"column":67,"offset":1329},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":1263},"end":{"line":10,"column":67,"offset":1329},"indent":[]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Digital Advertising: Google ads, social media ads …. essentially anything on the Internet ","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":1333},"end":{"line":11,"column":93,"offset":1423},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":1333},"end":{"line":11,"column":93,"offset":1423},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":1331},"end":{"line":11,"column":93,"offset":1423},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":1117},"end":{"line":11,"column":93,"offset":1423},"indent":[1,1,1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Advertising has a broader audience in mind, with the exception of digital advertising. Let’s look at billboard ads. They are designed to be shown to a lot, hoping to be acknowledged by a few. Meanwhile, digital ad campaign can pinpoint a specific group who views their ad. A Facebook or Instagram ad for example can target by age, geographic location, interests, occupations and so on. For digital advertisers, there is a wealth of information about their online audience readily available. ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1427},"end":{"line":13,"column":492,"offset":1918},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1427},"end":{"line":13,"column":492,"offset":1918},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Marketing basics","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":4,"offset":1925},"end":{"line":15,"column":20,"offset":1941},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1922},"end":{"line":15,"column":20,"offset":1941},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Marketing is not a quick campaign – it’s a process. Marketing works best when it can develop and promote a brand over time using a variety of methods and resources. Marketing is designed to get an audience interested in your business and its offerings while building a sense of community. The ultimate goal is to attract and retain a continually growing base of happy customers or clients. Looking at the big picture, advertising is just one component of an overarching marketing plan. Here are other examples of activities that help to market a business. ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1943},"end":{"line":16,"column":557,"offset":2499},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1943},"end":{"line":16,"column":557,"offset":2499},"indent":[]}},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"start":null,"spread":false,"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pricing","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":3,"offset":2505},"end":{"line":18,"column":10,"offset":2512},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":3,"offset":2505},"end":{"line":18,"column":10,"offset":2512},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":2503},"end":{"line":18,"column":10,"offset":2512},"indent":[]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Customer service  ","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":3,"offset":2516},"end":{"line":19,"column":21,"offset":2534},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":3,"offset":2516},"end":{"line":19,"column":21,"offset":2534},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":2514},"end":{"line":19,"column":21,"offset":2534},"indent":[]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Charity or community involvement  ","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":3,"offset":253